    "discriminators": [
     "Hail is a dense stochastic impact texture -- discrete ice pellets striking a hard surface -- not a hiss. Versus RAIN it has a brighter spectrum and a markedly higher crest factor, because each grain is a real transient rather than a droplet splash.",
     "Its grain onsets are stochastic, not periodic: onset_periodicity stays near zero, which separates it from any rhythmic mechanical texture.",
     "Versus WEATHER-STORM: a storm is a composite (wind + rain + thunder) and carries far more low-frequency energy and far more dynamic variation."
    ],
